                            <comment id="12615345" author="stack" created="Mon, 21 Jul 2008 18:13:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You probably already know this but, &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
$HADOOP_HOME/bin/hadoop fs -dus /HBASE.ROOTDIR
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;will give you the size an instance of hbase occupies on the filesytem (or &apos;$HADOOP_HOME/bin/hadoop fs -dus /HBASE.ROOTDIR/TABLENAME&apos; if you want size of a particular table).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You think we should show this in the metadata info in the UI?  The section which lists hbase version, hbase.rootdir, etc?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards number of splits, where would you like to see this?  Is it important? You can do a grep/count over the master logs.  What else would you like to see other than splits?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12615577" author="d4niel" created="Tue, 22 Jul 2008 11:10:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, using command line can gather the size in HDFS, im just wondering whether we can do this in API,  and not including the meta info dir.&lt;br/&gt;
for the number of splits, it&apos;s just a thought, we can have other information in metadata like the counts of rows, columns etc. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;im thinking about situations like in chained MR jobs, it&apos;s better to gather all the relative infor from API , instead of calling shell commands, isnt it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13178224" author="qwertymaniac" created="Sun, 1 Jan 2012 20:34:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You should be able to retrieve &apos;dus&apos; kind of results with Hadoop&apos;s FileSystem API itself. I think number of splits is a useful metric to show, but doesn&apos;t deserve an API. We can open a new JIRA if thats still not shown today.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
